The API shall accept the principal amount (P), interest rate (r), time (t), and number of times interest is compounded per year (n) as parameters, and return the compound interest using the formula A = P(1 + r/n)^(nt), where A is the amount after interest.
reverse_generated_requirement:
The system shall allow users to calculate the compound interest amount based on the provided principal, rate, time, and compounding frequency. Users should be able to enter a positive principal amount, a non-zero rate per year, a positive time period in years or months, and a compoundings per year value greater than zero. The system shall validate user input parameters and return an error response if any of these criteria are not met.

The system shall calculate the compound interest using the formula A = P(1 + r/n)^(nt), where A is the amount after interest, P is the principal, r is the rate per year, n is the number of compoundings per year, and t is the time period in years or months. The system shall use the `BigDecimal` class from Java's built-in library to handle decimal numbers with high precision.

The system shall return an error response if any input parameter is invalid or if there is an exception during calculation. The system shall also provide a response message indicating that the request was successful and providing the calculated interest amount.
